>\n                        <altIdentifier>\n                            <settlement/>\n                            <repository/>\n                            <idno type=\"old\"/>\n                        </altIdentifier>\n                    </msIdentifier>\n                    <msContents>\n                        <textLang mainLang=\"la\">Latin</textLang>\n                    </msContents>\n                    <physDesc>\n                        <objectDesc>\n                            <supportDesc>\n                                <support><p>Small plaque of grey marble (coarse, crystalline). In relation to the inscription the plaque is seemingly intact above, to the right and below, but broken on the left. The edges are rough, the rear rough and very irregular in depth. The surface is well finished wtih a bounding line incised vertically down the right margin of the text. Minor damage to the surface, upper right.</p>\n                                    <material ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble</material>\n                                    <objectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html\">plaque</objectType>\n                                    <dimensions>\n                                        <height unit=\"cm\">14.4-14.8</height>\n                                        <width unit=\"cm\">20.3 (max)</width>\n                                        <depth unit=\"cm\">3.8 (max)</depth>\n                                    </dimensions>\n                                </support>\n                                <condition ana=\"#condition.damaged\"/>\n\t\t    </supportDesc>\n                            <layoutDesc>\n                                <layout><p>Three lines of Latin letters, decreasing in size, and probably centred on the stone.</p>\n                                    <rs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled</rs>\n                                \t<damage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t</layout>\n                            </layoutDesc>\n                        </objectDesc>\n                        <handDesc>\n                            <handNote><p>Letters are somewhat irregular with some serifs and the M regularly extended above the apex. Multi-pointed interpuncts between words.</p>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">35-36</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">31-35</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line3\" to=\"line3\">Line 3</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\">17-23</height>\n                                </dimensions>\n                                <locus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>\n                                <dimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    <height unit=\"mm\"/>\n                                </dimensions>\n                            </handNote>\n                        </handDesc>\n                    </physDesc>\n                    <history>\n                        <origin>\n                            <origPlace>\n                                <placeName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462513\" cert=\"low\">Thermae Himeraeae</placeName>\t\t\n                                <placeName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/6539140\">Termini Imerese</placeName>\n                            \t<geo>37.98365, 13.69555</geo>\n\t\t</origPlace>\n                            <origDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0001\" notAfter-custom=\"0300\">Imperial</origDate>\n                        </origin>\n                        <provenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" notAfter=\"1838\">First recorded in Termini by Romano, as being in the casa del civico magistrato; subsequently seen by Mommsen in the museum.</provenance>\n                        <provenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\">Prag, 2022-07-06, on display on the ground floor of the museum.</provenance>\n                        <acquisition/>\n                    </history>\n                </msDesc>\n            </sourceDesc>\n        </fileDesc>\n        <encodingDesc>\n             <p>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines</p>\n             <xi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 <xi:fallback>\n                     <p>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values</p>\n                 </xi:fallback>\n             </xi:include>\n\t  <xi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     <xi:fallback>\n\t       <p>ISicily glyphs authority list</p>\n\t     </xi:fallback>\n\t   </xi:include>\n         </encodingDesc>\n        <profileDesc>\n            <calendarDesc>\n                <calendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    <p>Julian Calendar</p>\n                </calendar>\n            </calendarDesc>\n            <langUsage>\n                <language ident=\"en\">English</language>\n                <language ident=\"it\">Italian</language>\n                <language ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek</language>\n                <language ident=\"la\">Latin</language>\n                <language ident=\"he\">Hebrew</language>\n                <language ident=\"phn\">Phoenician</language>\n                <language ident=\"xpu\">Punic</language>\n                <language ident=\"osc\">Oscan</language>\n                <language ident=\"xly\">Elymian</language>\n                <language ident=\"scx\">Sikel</language>\n                <language ident=\"sxc\">Sikan</language>\n            </langUsage>\n            <textClass>\n                <keywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    <term ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary</term>\n                </keywords>\n            </textClass>\n        </profileDesc>\n        <revisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            <listChange>\n                   <change when=\"2016-12-03\" who=\"#JCu\">James Cummings autogenerated EpiDoc output from database</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-05\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova normalised Unicode</change>\n            \t   <change when=\"2020-10-08\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova updated list of languages</change>\n                   <change when=\"2020-10-12\" who=\"#VM\">Valentina Mignosa encoded text division, cleaned up the autogenerated text and checked the edition</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2020-11-20\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova added EDCS numbers</change>\n\t\t<change when=\"2020-11-26\" who=\"#SS\">Simona Stoyanova restructured bibliography</change>\n\t    <change when=\"2020-12-17\" who=\"#system\">Updated Zenodo DOI</change>\n            \t<change when=\"2021-01-19\" who=\"#SS\">renumbered files, uris and references</change>\n                <change when=\"2024-07-26\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag revised file from autopsy and added image</change>\n\t</listChange>\n        </revisionDesc>\n    </teiHeader>\n    <facsimile>\n        <surface type=\"front\">\n            <graphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic000195_tiled.tif\" height=\"2249px\" width=\"2790px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-10</desc>\n            </graphic>\n            <graphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic000195.jpg\" height=\"2249px\" width=\"2790px\">\n                <desc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2018-07-10</desc>\n            </graphic>\n         </surface>\n    </facsimile>\n    <text>\n        <body>\n            <div type=\"edition\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"la\" resp=\"#VM #JP\">\n                <ab>\n                    <lb n=\"1\"/><gap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/><w part=\"F\"><unclear>M</unclear></w> <g ref=\"#interpunct\">·</g> <persName type=\"attested\"><name><hi rend=\"ligature\">Ma</hi>rgar</name></persName>\n                    <lb n=\"2\"/><supplied reason=\"lost\"><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>ixit</ex></expan></supplied> <expan><abbr><unclear>a</unclear></abbr><ex>nnis</ex></expan> <g ref=\"#interpunct\">·</g> <num value=\"4\">IIII</num> <g ref=\"#interpunct\">·</g> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>ensibus</ex></expan> <g ref=\"#interpunct\">·</g> <num value=\"11\">XI</num>\n                    <lb n=\"3\"/><expan><abbr>d</abbr><ex>iebus</ex></expan> <g ref=\"#interpunct\">·</g> <num value=\"7\">VII</num>\n                </ab>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"apparatus\">\n                <listApp>\n                    <app><note>Text from autopsy</note></app>\n                    <app loc=\"1\"><note>Mommsen, Bivona: [D(is)] M(anibus]</note></app>\n                </listApp>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <p>... Margar lived four years, 11 months, 7 days.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                <p>Either Margaris or Margarita is likely as the name at the end of line 1 (either continuing into line 2, or simply abbreviated). Mommsen, followed by Bivona, opted to read the initial letter as M (difficult to see what else it could be) and to interpret it as part of D(is) M(anibus). As Bivona notes, this is unusual inline with the name. It is at least as likely that Margar is preceded by a nomen, albeit one that has, like Margar, been abbreviated of its ending.</p>\n            </div>\n            <div type=\"bibliography\">\n                <listBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    <bibl>\n                        <author>Romano</author>\n                        <date>1838</date>\n                        <citedRange>115 no.37</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/25ZN5T5X\"/>\n                        <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001618\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001618</ref>\n                    </bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"CIL\">\n                        <citedRange>\n                            <ref target=\"http://arachne.uni-koeln.de/books/CILv10pII1883\">10.7420</ref>\n                        </citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/GQN8UZSI\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000589</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl type=\"corpus\" n=\"ILMusTermini\">\n                        <citedRange>118</citedRange>\n                        <ptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/JCV85C79\"/>\n                    <ref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002137</ref></bibl>\n                    <bibl/>\n                </listBibl>\n\t   <listBibl type=\"discussion\"><bibl/></listBibl>\n            </div>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n",
